	• Git is a versioning Tool - it gives the details of all the activities done on a resource even fetch them.
	• :git init -> execute it in the folder which you want the git to do version control.
	• .git is hidden inside that folder
	• The folder where we executed git init will allow us to run git commands and access through terminal as well
	• Branch - the folder we initiated is the master/main branch. When we create a new branch - it also has the contents of the main branch.
	• Commit - making the changes to the staged file. Before committing we have to add the file to the staging location/repo
	• Git add make the untrackable file staged.
	• Once it is added it can be committed. It will make the file trackable.
	• To commit delete also you have to add and then commit to delete it permanently.
	• We can revert the deleted file by using its hash id.
	• By default the git folder in local is called master. 
	• In Github it is called origin/main.
	• To publish my local commit to github execute push
	• To get the changes from github to local use git pull
